title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson, S&W Model M&P 15 Sport 5.56mm 16” Barrel 811036 022188145663
postcontent: The M&P 15 lower and upper receivers are made from 7075 T6 Aluminum, fully forged in house by Smith & Wesson. Included with the lower: the single piece, solid forged, non-removable, over sized for gloves trigger guard. A typical six position telescoping stock is standard, along with sling mounts allowing for single or double point sling attachment. There is even a bayonet lug just in case. All of the M&P15 Sport’s parts are interchangeable with the rest of their AR15 product line.The M&P15 Sport’s barrel isn’t an M4 cut. This cut in the barrel will allow to mount a M203 grenade launcher. This additional cut also does not help the harmonics of the barrel. We think this a advantage that will help accuracy but will ultimately come down to the ammo used. The Smith sports a full profile barrel of American 4140 Steel. The bolt carrier and gas key are chromed, and the barrel sports their Melonite coating. Smith claims that the bare bones approach has no effect on durability. There have been reviews with this rifle firing 85,000 rounds of various brands of ammunition without any visible damage to the Melonite finish. We have found this to be a very reliable platform and so have law enforcement and countless other agencies. The engineers at Smith and Wesson made a great call when deciding to reduce the cost of their AR15 by not including a forward assist most shooters don’t use forward assists often, and when they do, it can lead to a dangerous situation. When using a forward assist, there is a potential for an inexperienced shooter to use the forward assist to jam the bolt forward when it is not the right response to a jam. A forward assist on any AR15 could cause the cartridge to get super stuck in the rifle. The original Mil Spec on the AR-15 did not include the forward assist. Smith and Wesson made another good call deciding not adding a dust cover to their M&P Sport AR15. Most AR15 shooters have little or no need for a dust cover because they’re firing from safe and clean environments. The M&P Sport is mostly used at shooting ranges, hunting, etc. In this day and age everyone is looking for the best value out there and with out any doubt this is it, you are defiantly not paying for any unneccessary features on this model. 30 Round PMAG MagazineAdjustable Front and Rear Sights6-Position Telescopic Butt StockChrome-lined Gas Key and Bolt Carrier16" Barrel 1 in 9” 4140 Steel 5.56 mm NATOReceiver 7075 T6 Aluminum Hard Coat Black AnodizedUPC:REDACTED63MFG:811036

title: For Sale:  Savage Model 10 Precision Carbine/308 Win/5r rifling/Minox ZA5 Scope
postcontent:
Ok, I have a Savage Model 10 PC in 308 Win. This particular one was a distributors special with the 20" long fluted and threaded barrel with 5r rifling and a 1 in 11.25" twist. It has the digicamo stock, detachable 4+1 round drop mag, Harris style 6-9" bipod, a Blackhawk cheek riser for the buttstock, and it is threaded 5/8x24 tpi with thread protector and currently wears a surefire socom muzzle brake.( I also have an AAC 51T Blackout muzzle brake if you'd prefer it).  It has the adjustable accutruigger( set around 3lbs right now but can be adjusted down to 1.5 lbs I believe), digicamo accustock with aluminum bedding block, etc. It's a sub moa rifle all day long with decent ammo, and I've only put about 100 rounds through it, all factory match grade rounds with thorough cleaning and maintenance after each trip to the range.

Also included is a Minox ZA5 2-10x40mm scope. It has the XR-BDC reticle, 5 times magnification, a 1" main tube, it has amazingly clear and crisp German Schott glass, and it's made in the USA. So, you really do get the best of both worlds with this scope. It's mounted in Warne scope rings, and I do have the boxes, manuals, lens cleaning cloth, and everything else that came with all this.

If interested, I also have a ton of all factory/no reloads, match grade ammo too for an additional charge if interested.

For interested parties, shoot me a reply and I'd be more than happy to text or email you detailed pictures of everything. If you're around the area we can meet in person too if you want so you can inspect everything and shoot it if you want before purchase. I'd prefer to do a local deal but will ship in the CONUS through an FFL, as long as you cover those fees.

Im selling this to help fund a different 308 rifle (Semi auto AR10 platform)  for my wife and would prefer to sell the rifle with the scope and everything else on it as a package deal. It has been an amazingly fun, smooth and accurate rifle for me,ands I was going to throw it in an XLR chassis, but life happened and the wife wants another toy...! So, I'm open to reasonable offers but please NO LOW BALLLING!!! This is a pick up and shoot package deal with everything you already need. For everything: rifle, scope, scope rings, muzzle brake, and bipod, I'd like to get $1150. I feel that this price is pretty good for the whole enchilada. For the right offer/price, I can throw in some brand new all factory match grade ammo, either range or hunting rounds, your choice, and a 46" long Drago soft drag bag/double rifle case. Also included is shooting/drop data for 168gr rounds.

This is accomplished by means of a piston contained inside of a cylinder located under the barrel that opposes the rearward motion of the slide until the gas pressure has declined after the bullet has left the barrel.
